    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but my doctor is always so rushed and basically just tells me \"stay the course\" without really explaining why. it feels like a lot of extra medication if my blood work has been fine for months. if i were to just test it out for a week on 2mg and see how i feel, would that be a massive risk or is it pretty standard to taper down when someone is stable?",
